---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCapture from '../../components/EmailCapture.astro';
import FAQ from '../../components/FAQ.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Island Hopping Malaysia — Langkawi, Tioman, Perhentians & More';
const pageDescription = 'The complete guide to island hopping in Malaysia. Langkawi archipelago tours, Perhentian Islands snorkeling, Tioman Island diving, and how to plan island-to-island routes.';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Island Hopping', url: '/island-hopping/' },
];

const islands = [
  {
    name: 'Langkawi',
    tagline: 'Duty-free island with a dramatic cable car and the best island hopping in west coast Malaysia',
    region: 'West Malaysia',
    slug: 'langkawi',
    bestFor: ['First-timers', 'Families', 'Duty-free shopping', 'Cable car and Sky Bridge', 'New Year\'s Eve beach parties'],
    season: 'Nov–Apr (dry season). Closed: Jul–Sep (rough seas)',
    hopping: 'Half-day island hopping tours hit Pulau Dayang Bunting (freshwater lake), Pulau Beras Basah (white sand), and eagle feeding at Singa Besar. RM35-50/person.',
    icon: '🏝️',
  },
  {
    name: 'Perhentian Islands',
    tagline: 'The clearest water in Malaysia, right next to Thailand-quality coral reefs',
    region: 'East Coast Peninsular',
    slug: 'perhentian-islands',
    bestFor: ['Snorkeling and diving', 'Backpacker island life', 'Turtles year-round', 'Budget travelers', 'PADI dive courses'],
    season: 'Mar–Oct. CLOSED Nov–Feb (monsoon season)',
    hopping: 'Day boat trips circle both Perhentian Besar and Kecil with snorkel stops at turtle bays, coral gardens, and shark point. RM30-50/person.',
    icon: '🤿',
  },
  {
    name: 'Tioman Island',
    tagline: 'Jungle-covered volcanic island with pristine coral and no resorts in sight from the beach',
    region: 'East Coast Peninsular',
    slug: 'tioman-island',
    bestFor: ['Diving (visibility up to 20m)', 'Jungle trekking across the island', 'Remote beach life', 'Snorkeling off the coast', 'Escape from mainland Malaysia'],
    season: 'Mar–Oct. CLOSED Nov–Feb (monsoon season)',
    hopping: 'Water taxis connect Tioman\'s five main villages. RM10-20 between beaches. Day snorkeling trips available from Salang and Tekek.',
    icon: '🌴',
  },
];

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: 'Which is better for island hopping — Langkawi or Perhentian Islands?',
    answer: 'Different strengths. Langkawi suits families and those who want comfort, duty-free shopping, and the cable car alongside beach and island tours. The Perhentian Islands are a better choice for snorkeling, diving, and backpacker-style island life — the water clarity is significantly better. Both are closed to tourism Nov-Feb due to monsoon.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When is the best time for island hopping in Malaysia?',
    answer: 'The east coast islands (Perhentians, Tioman, Redang) are open March to October only — the northeast monsoon closes them November to February. Langkawi on the west coast is best November to April but open year-round. If visiting in November to February, Langkawi and the west coast are your only island hopping options.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I get to the Perhentian Islands?',
    answer: 'Take a bus from KL to Kuala Besut jetty (5-6 hours, RM35-50), then a speedboat to the islands (30-40 minutes, RM70 return). The total journey from KL is about 6-7 hours. There are no flights. The easiest route includes an overnight in Kota Bharu if arriving late.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I do a multi-island trip in Malaysia?',
    answer: 'Yes, though the logistics depend on which coast you\'re visiting. On the east coast, you can do both the Perhentians and Tioman in one trip (they\'re a few hours apart). Langkawi on the west coast can be combined with Penang by ferry (2.5 hours). Combining east and west coast islands requires crossing the peninsula and is better as two separate trips.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is island hopping in Malaysia safe?',
    answer: 'Yes, with standard precautions. All operators use licensed boats. Check weather conditions before booking — monsoon season waves are dangerous and tours are cancelled or unavailable. Always wear a life jacket on open water crossings. Snorkeling with a buddy is standard practice. Don\'t book the cheapest boat you find at the jetty — use your accommodation or a licensed operator.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  pageType="homepage"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
  <section class="pillar-hero">
    <div class="container-content pillar-hero-inner">
      <p class="pillar-eyebrow">Island Guide</p>
      <h1 class="pillar-title">Island Hopping Malaysia</h1>
      <p class="pillar-subtitle">Langkawi's dramatic archipelago, the Perhentians' glass-clear coral waters, and Tioman's jungle-draped volcanic shores. Malaysia's islands don't get the attention of Thailand's — which means more reef for you.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-content section-padding">
    <div class="pillar-intro">
      <p>Malaysia's islands divide neatly into two coasts. The west coast (Langkawi) faces the Andaman Sea and stays open year-round. The east coast islands (Perhentians, Tioman, Redang) face the South China Sea and close entirely from November to February when the northeast monsoon makes them inaccessible. Plan your timing accordingly.</p>
      <p>What the Malaysian islands lack in mass tourism infrastructure, they make up for in quality. The Perhentian Islands' water clarity rivals anything in Thailand at a fraction of the cost. Tioman is one of the top 10 dive destinations in Asia. Langkawi's island hopping circuit takes you past dramatic limestone karst emerging from flat green water.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="pillar-section-title">Malaysia's Best Islands</h2>

    <div class="islands-grid">
      {islands.map((island) => (
        <div class="island-card">
          <div class="island-header">
            <span class="island-icon">{island.icon}</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="island-name">{island.name}</h3>
              <p class="island-region">{island.region}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="island-tagline">{island.tagline}</p>

          <div class="island-bestfor">
            <p class="island-meta-label">Best for:</p>
            <ul class="island-bestfor-list">
              {island.bestFor.map((b) => <li>{b}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="island-season">
            <span class="island-meta-label">Season:</span> {island.season}
          </div>

          <div class="island-hopping-info">
            <p class="island-meta-label">Island hopping:</p>
            <p>{island.hopping}</p>
          </div>

          <a href={`/destinations/${island.slug}/`} class="island-link">Full guide to {island.name}</a>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="pillar-section">
      <h2>How to Plan an Island Hopping Trip in Malaysia</h2>
      <p>The most common mistake is booking an east coast island trip in November or December (monsoon season) — many first-time visitors don't realize the islands physically close during this period. Always check season status before booking flights or accommodation.</p>
      <p>For a first-time Malaysia island trip, Langkawi is the safest bet year-round and combines well with Penang (ferry or flight). For the best snorkeling and diving, target the Perhentian Islands in May-August when visibility peaks and water is calmest. Tioman suits dedicated divers who want less company than the Perhentians attract.</p>
      <p>Getting between islands in Malaysia is mostly by speedboat. The west-to-east crossing (Langkawi to Perhentians, for example) requires going back to the mainland and across — plan this as two separate trip legs rather than a continuous hop.</p>
    </div>

    <EmailCapture
      leadMagnet="Get the Free Malaysia Island Hopping Guide"
      description="Complete island hopping itineraries for Malaysia — Langkawi, Perhentians, Tioman, and the hidden islands off the beaten path."
      bullets={[
        'Season calendar — which islands are open when',
        'Ferry and speedboat connections between all major islands',
        'Best snorkeling and diving spots with depth and visibility data',
        '3-day, 5-day, and 7-day island hopping itineraries with prices',
      ]}
      guideTag="pillar-island-hopping"
    />

    <FAQ items={faqItems} />
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pillar-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0C4A6E 0%, #0369A1 50%, #0EA5E9 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 80px 0 60px;
  }
  .pillar-hero-inner { text-align: center; }
  .pillar-eyebrow {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    opacity: 0.75;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .pillar-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .pillar-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pillar-intro {
    max-width: 75ch;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-12);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-slate);
  }
  .pillar-intro p { margin-bottom: 1em; }
  .pillar-section-title {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
  }
  .islands-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .islands-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  .island-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    border: 1px solid #EBE4D8;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .island-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .island-icon { font-size: 2rem; line-height: 1; }
  .island-name { font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-deep-night); margin: 0 0 4px; }
  .island-region { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #0369A1; margin: 0; }
  .island-tagline { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-slate); line-height: 1.5; font-style: italic; margin: 0; }
  .island-meta-label { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-deep-night); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .island-bestfor-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 16px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .island-season { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-slate); }
  .island-hopping-info p:not(.island-meta-label) { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-slate); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0; }
  .island-link { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #0369A1; text-decoration: none; margin-top: auto; }
  .island-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .pillar-section {
    max-width: 75ch;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-12);
  }
  .pillar-section h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
  }
  .pillar-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 1em;
  }
</style>
